text: It was a very bad experience. On the second day of my visit, I was told that the numbers had been allocated. I came back tomorrow morning. When I came to queue at 8.50am the next morning, I was told that there were no more numbers. I ignored him and continued to queue, but I was cut in line.

This work efficiency is not only poor but also poor
I really have nothing to say
No matter where you go, the room is the same
The attitude is extremely bad. It takes a whole day to open an account. How big is this bank?
How many counters do you have to change to open an account and get a card? ! ! ! Your time is time, but other people’s time is not time? ?

I arrived at 8 o'clock in the morning, and the number was queued until 1:30. The processing basically did not follow the time schedule. It depends on who occupied the stool earlier. I took the number at 1:30, and when I arrived at 1 o'clock, I asked the staff, and the staff said that the number was only processed at 1 o'clock. The people who queued up at two o'clock are almost in, but I'm still sitting on a stool waiting. I don't understand what the time you gave me is for?

The work efficiency is so poor. This is the only place on the island where you can handle business. There are too many people and you can’t even get a number. You have to go to the queue at seven o’clock in the morning. This is the most troublesome place in Singapore to do business.

The business hours are Monday to Friday 8:30-16:30 and Saturday 8:30-13:00. About four to five hundred people can handle business every day, so it is best to queue up before 7:30 to get the number. Passport and permit are required.
